# Layer import direction

Allowed imports (one-way only):

```
apps         -> @core, @platform, @domains, @integrations
integrations -> @core, @platform, @domains
domains      -> @core, @platform
platform     -> @core
core         -> @core only (leaf)
```

## Do

- Import from the **alias barrel** (`@domains/identity`, `@platform/auth`), not
  deep relative paths into another lib.
- When `platform` needs domain knowledge, define a **port/token** (like
  `ACCESS_CHECKER` in `@platform/auth`) and let the app bind a domain impl.
- Re-export a lib's public surface from its `src/index.ts`.

## Don't

- Don't import "up": `platform` must not import `@domains/*` or `@integrations/*`;
  `domains` must not import `@integrations/*` or another `@domains/*`; `core` must
  not import `@platform/*`.
- Don't import one app from another (`apps/*` are isolated deployables).
- Don't bypass the barrel by reaching into another lib's `src/...` internals.

Enforced by `npm run check:layers` (`scripts/check-layer-rules.ts`) and the ESLint
rules in `tools/eslint-rules` (`no-cross-app-import`, etc.).
